Verilator supports 
```<code class="c">
typedef struct packed {
     bit [10:0]  expo;
     bit         sign;
     bit [51:0]  mant;
} FP;
</code>
```
I wonder where packed structs can be used: It seems it can be used instead of _wire_, but can it also be used to define a _reg_?
